And I'm not sure. I know so many people that would totally kick my ass for this. I'm not sure that I mind thought. I never thought that hearing that would be so awesome. Haha. Oh well. What ev.

So I'm sitting there staring at my computer, having a freaking panic attack, thinking, "who the hell does she think she is??" So, now I'm all light headed and I'm shaking.

Ugh...more later...I have to go..

OK...bored again. Really want to text John, really trying to control myself. OK..I have to talk about something else now...So Tonys a total creep, but what else is new. This weekend was somewhat odd.

Friday: I did pretty much nothing but eat junk food and watch tv while trying to ignore the fact that (because of all the snow) 'Night of 1,000 Stars' was that night...blech. I did a pretty good job at ignoring it, well, the junk food helped a lot. Ha.

Saturday: I helped with 'Breakfast with Santa,' but that only lasted two hours for me, so I was up and dressed at 12 o'clock on a Saturday with nothing to do. Totally not like the exact opposit of me. So I went home, cleaned my room a little(not as much as I should have because it still looks like crap). Then got online and talked to Brittany for a little while. I told her about John, ahh. We decided that we were going to call him later. I was really freaked out about it because I thought that they were going to fight or something and I would still be on the phone. Weird. But they didn't. Thank God. It actually really wasn't that bad. Once we all got over the shock that we were all actually talking on the phone and not killing eachother, it was alright. We mite have actually hade one or two normal conversations. Must finish this later...

I wish it was Friday, but its only Thursay. *cries* We are watching Elf. I love that movie. Hehe. Well this morning was kinda weird. I swear Tony was everywhere I went! Ahh! It was really scary...Haha. OK...not scary, just really, really weird. After first hour I was talking to Paul (also weird):

Him: I have Tony's hat. I'm going to make him pay me for it next hour.
Me: *trying to remember if it was that ugly white hat with all the stupid dollar signs all over it* (and yes, by the way it was) Ha. Have fun with that.
Him: I will.
Me: Personaly...If it was me I would burn it, but like I said, thats just me. (hehe)
Him: Yea, I know he kinda...
Me: Yea.
Him: If you ever need to talk about it-
Me: No, no, Its alright. Im fine.

Hmm....Thats all I could think. Just "hmm." So while I was thinking about what that ment, I got was forced  to listen to Michelle talk about all the different names she has for Jacobs penis. Great. (That girl has one wild imagination) She just kept talking and all of a sudden her eyes get really big, so I turned around and Jacob was right behind me. Ha. Awkward, but still Ha. I'll have to finish this is Computer Apps. 4th hour.

OK...so fourth hour is finaly here. It took forever though. So now that I've heard all of the "lunch gossip" of the day (Don't you just love abosolutly want to kill High School?) Well last I had heard Tony was dating another freshman (I think I heard this Tuesday? ... What ever, not too long ago) Well apparenty he broke up with her, they only dated for about a day. Heh. Of coarse after I heard this I immediatly busted out in my high pitched, squeaky, almost evil laugh that I just cannot control. I got very weird staires form every one at my table. Hehe.

So me and Lauren (Cashon) were standing out side of our classes waiting for the bell to fing after lunch:

Her: I'm bored, say something!
Me: Umm....Oh! (I was kinda hyper...) Tony was like (hints the like) every where this morning! When we were out side he was there, we went up stairs and walked around and I turned around and he was talking to Caitlyn! Then we went back down stairs and he was there again! It was like "How the hell are you dont that!?!"
Her: Did you ever think that is happening for a reason?
Me: No! (That really didn't ever accur to me)
Her: I'll talk to him about it tomorrow, I have lunch with him both days.
Me: Lucky you...

I really don't want her to talk to him about it (what ever "it" is). I can handle this "it" myself, but right after she said that (and I made a smart ass comment) the bell rang and it was too late. So, of coarse, all 3rd hour I had that stupid idea in my head. What does she think shes going to say to him anyways? "Lindsay's paranioed," or maybe "Lindsay's stupid." Take you pick, they both seem to apply.

OK...so French next hour. I made cookies. Yay! Just one more day in this week...Whoo! This week has been so long. Ahh!

OK...We get out in less than an hour. Totally awesome. I love snow. Ugh, I just head to announcements about ten minutes ago. All I heard was "Blah, Blah, Blah, Key Club, 'Night of A Thousand Stars' tomorrow, Blah , Blah, Blah." Now I feel like I'm going to throw up. I felt really light headed. Like if someone were to just barely push me I would fall over and not be able to get up. I do know one thing; I sure as hell am not going to be any where near Main Street tomorrow. There's no way. 

I'm in FBLA and we are watching Drum Line. So all I hear is drums. It reminds me of my sisters competitions at the Dome. They were awesome. If we went somewhere awesome and not just Hannibal, Quincy, and stupid crap like that I would probably still be in band. What ever. It doesn't really matter any more. 

I am so happy that it's going to snow. That almost makes up for the fact that it is December tomorrow. Oh well, everything will be alright I guess. I just need to give it time. Hopefully, somehow, the snow will make this all just go away. Snow does that sometimes. 

...28 minutes left. Not that I'm counting down or anything. Eww, Channel One. I Hate Channel One. Blech. About 10 minutes left now...I guess I'll go do something at least a little productive...Maybe.

 - Lindsay
